name: Monumen Operasi Lintas Laut Jawa - Bali
address: RC4V+R8P, Gilimanuk, Melaya, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82252, Indonesia
review 1: A really nice host and a pretty place to do a brake
review 2:
Lovely little place we visited for half hour To have a break and stretch out.

Didn’t learn a lot about this place but it has a army vehicle/weapon so guessing it’s something to do with that. Very clean but old place. Not a lot of visitors when we went there.
review 3:
Old dilapidated monument, with weaponry show that did not relate with what the event was (Russian made 1960-ish gun at the monument that commemorate 1946 independence war). However as Indonesian, it is good to pay respect to the unsung hero that departed before us in defending the sovereignty (80+ departed from the 240+ men) and understanding the meaning of freedom and independence.

It not an attractive tourism spot though, and all the information is in Bahasa Indonesia only.
review 4: There is not much to see. You are asked to give a donation which are usually between 100.000 and 250.000 which is way too much for what you get to see.
review 5: Beautiful but sadly no explanation about this monument

name: Campgrounds Hall West Bali National Park
address: RC5R+RXG, Jl. Raya Denpasar - Gilimanuk, Gilimanuk, Kec. Melaya, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali 82252, Indonesia
review 1: great area for camping with family and friends! they provide you lots of toilets so worry not. the place is quite neat and clean. you can see lots of jalak bali here!
review 2:
After reading reviews about this national park we didn't get there. Because we met scams by bus in Gilimanuk and it was so horrible.

Why I wrote this? Do something with it!
review 3: The campground doesn't really exists anymore! There are no facilities and if you like to stay anyway you have to pay the National Park fee of 200.000IDR/person (on weekends the double price)!!! The location itself it's between the very busy and noisy road no.1 and the not very nice beach. So no way to stay there any more!
review 4: Very nice place, silent and a step into the beach
review 5: A not-so-bad camping place. But it got some unmaintained building (which i guess usually used for meet-up place) and it makes this place looked ugly and creepy at night. It also got access to a beach, which is also unmaintained very well, it's always dirty..

name: Monument Gilimanuk
address: RC4V+R8Q, Gilimanuk, Melaya, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82252, Indonesia
